The premises currently includes:

- Large open plan area

If you would like further detail or would like to arrange an inspection please call, Tom Bennett on 0430 924 629 or Peter Mangraviti on 0419 750 350.

CBRE is pleased to present Little Zak’s Academy, Artarmon, a prime three level child care investment in a core employment hub within Sydney’s North Shore. 

6 Clarendon Street, Artarmon is currently leased to Affinity Education Group, who own and operate 167 childcare centres nationally. Trading as Little Zak’s Academy Artarmon, the premium childcare provider offers a secure lease with options until 2052.

Little Zak's Artarmon benefits from the following key attributes:

• Net Income: $1,260,000 p.a.
• Brand new triple net 10-year lease to leading childcare provider Affinity Education Group with options to 2052
• Fixed annual 3.5% rental increases
• Childcare operating with approval for 210 places
• Modern fit out with depreciation benefits
• Well performing growth suburb with a thriving child care market
• Total building NLA: 3,222sqm*
• Located in the Artarmon employment hub within 1.1km* of the St Leonards Train Station and Artarmon Train Station

The property is to be offered by way of expressions of interest closing Wednesday, 06 December 2017 at 4 PM (AEST).

CBRE in conjunction with Raine & Horne Commercial are pleased to offer 50 Broughton Road, Artarmon, NSW for sale via an Expressions of Interest Campaign.

Situated in Artarmon the asset represents a unique opportunity to acquire a premium fully leased office/ warehouse asset of substantial scale. 

Key Features
+ Secure net income of $646,890.57 pa (as at 1 November 2019
+ Strong 4% annual reviews
+ Committed long term tenant has been in occupation for 14 yrs
+ 47 basement car spaces
+ 0.7KM to Artarmon train station
+ 8.6Km to the Sydney CBD

Due to its proximity to the CBD, high-quality improvements and exposure to The Gore Hill Freeway, this asset has a blue-chip leasing history with Boehringer Ingelheim, Stryker and now VOIP having occupied the property over the last 25 years.

With a secure income stream and a passing net rental of $646,890.57 + GST (as at 1 November 2019), this opportunity allows for purchasers to acquire a defensive investment that will benefit from the continued strong rental growth for well located, North Shore Industrial properties.

For sale via Expressions of Interest campaign closing Thursday 5th December 2019 at 4.00pm
